{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ac341204-43e5-4175-8f70-d69e7985cc88","content":"The directory is empty — no existing files. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Compiled Bindings in .NET MAUI\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings. This tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, so all `{Binding}` expressions are validated **at build time**.\n\n### SettingsPage.xaml — before → after\n\nThe only change needed is adding the `x:DataType` attribute:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### How it catches errors at build time\n\n1. **Typos are build errors.** If you write `{Binding Themee}`, the compiler emits:\n\n   ```\n   error XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n   ```\n\n2. **Type mismatches are caught.** Binding an `int` property to a control expecting a different type will warn or error.\n\n3. **Enable `$(StrictMode)` for even stricter checks** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n### Key rules to remember\n\n| Rule | Why |\n|---|---|\n| `x:DataType` can go on any element, not just the page | Scope it to `DataTemplate` entries for `CollectionView` items, etc. |\n| Use `x:DataType=\"\"` (empty string) to **opt out** locally | Needed for dynamic bindings like `{Binding .}` on untyped contexts |\n| Compiled bindings are faster at runtime | They skip reflection entirely |\n\nThat single `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute is all you need — the XAML compiler does the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17c7333c-41ce-4feb-925c-9bbd8cf1f6d6","outputTokens":737,"requestId":"143C:1521A3:6A49466:729A496:6A03CBBD"},"id":"f6458b81-6d2d-459e-9a31-fab40a845f7b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:36.970Z","parentId":"331d653a-f27c-494e-bf1e-aae8e272c987"}
